             Bloomberg's William Pesek speaks from
Tokyo with Bloomberg's Susan Li about microfinance lending.  
 SKS Microfinance Ltd., the Indian lender backed by George 
Soros, will raise the maximum 16.3 billion rupees ($353 million)
sought in an initial public offering, according to two people 
with knowledge of the matter. (William Pesek is a Bloomberg News
columnist. The opinions expressed are his own. Source: 
Bloomberg)  
